  "chapter": {
    "number": 40,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "I Waited Patiently for the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "For the choirmaster. A Psalm of David."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I waited patiently for the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He inclined to me and heard my cry.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He lifted me up from the pit of despair,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "out of the miry clay;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He set my feet upon a rock,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and made my footsteps firm.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He put a new song in my mouth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a hymn of praise to our God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Many will see and fear",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and put their trust in the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blessed is the man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who has made the LORD his trust,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who has not turned to the proud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor to those who lapse into falsehood.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4362
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Many, O LORD my God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are the wonders You have done,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the plans You have for us—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "none can compare to You—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "if I proclaim and declare them,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are more than I can count.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sacrifice and offering You did not desire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but my ears You have opened.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4363
          },
          {
            "text": "Burnt offerings and sin offerings",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "You did not require.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then I said, “Here I am, I have come—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it is written about me in the scroll:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I delight to do Your will, O my God;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4364
          },
          {
            "text": "Your law is within my heart.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I proclaim righteousness in the great assembly;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "behold, I do not seal my lips,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as You, O LORD, do know.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have not covered up Your righteousness in my heart;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have declared Your faithfulness and salvation;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have not concealed Your loving devotion and faithfulness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the great assembly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O LORD, do not withhold Your mercy from me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Your loving devotion and faithfulness will always guard me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For evils without number surround me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my sins have overtaken me, so that I cannot see.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They are more than the hairs of my head,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my heart has failed within me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be pleased, O LORD, to deliver me;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "hurry, O LORD, to help me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May those who seek my life",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "be ashamed and confounded;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "may those who wish me harm",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "be repelled and humiliated.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May those who say to me, “Aha, aha!”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "be appalled at their own shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May all who seek You",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rejoice and be glad in You;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "may those who love Your salvation",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "always say, “The LORD be magnified!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But I am poor and needy;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may the Lord think of me.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You are my helper and deliverer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O my God, do not delay.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
